## ✖ dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()

set.seed(1)
sim_mean_sd = function(n_obs, mu = 2, sigma = 3) {
  
  x = rnorm(n_obs, mean = mu, sd = sigma)
   
  tibble(
    mu_hat = mean(x),
    sigma_hat = sd(x)
  )
} 
sim_mean_sd(n_obs = 30)
## # A tibble: 1 × 2
##   mu_hat sigma_hat
##    <dbl>     <dbl>
## 1   2.25      2.77

for loop

output = vector("list", length = 100)

for (i in 1:100){
  
  output[[i]] = sim_mean_sd(n_obs = 30)
  
}

bind_rows(output) %>% 
  view

list columns

sim_results_df =  
  expand_grid(
    sample_size = 30,
    iteration = 1:100
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    estimate_df = map(sample_size, sim_mean_sd)
  ) %>% 
  unnest(estimate_df)
sim_results_df %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = mu_hat)) + 
  geom_density()

changing the sample size

sim_results_df =  
  expand_grid(
    sample_size = c(30, 60, 120, 240),
    iteration = 1:1000
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    estimate_df = map(sample_size, sim_mean_sd)
  ) %>% 
  unnest(estimate_df) %>% 
  view()
 sim_results_df %>%
  mutate(
    sample_size = str_c("n = ", sample_size),
    sample_size = fct_inorder(sample_size)) %>%
   ggplot(aes(x = sample_size, y = mu_hat, fill = sample_size)) + 
  geom_violin()

change something else

sim_results_df =  
  expand_grid(
    sample_size = c(30, 60, 120, 240),
    true_sigma = c(6,  3),
    iteration = 1:1000
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    estimate_df = 
      map2(.x = sample_size, .y = true_sigma, ~sim_mean_sd(n_obs = .x, sigma = .y))
  ) %>% 
  unnest(estimate_df) %>% 
  view()
sim_results_df %>%
  mutate(
    sample_size = str_c("n = ", sample_size),
    sample_size = fct_inorder(sample_size)) %>%
   ggplot(aes(x = sample_size, y = mu_hat, fill = sample_size)) + 
  geom_violin() +
  facet_grid(. ~true_sigma)
